args:
With the help of faerie magic, Mascula is able
to control his body remotely while remaining
inside Laxi, and he uses this newfound skill to
wipe out the androids. Just then, the group
receives word that Jinlorda has started a raid
on the Sacred Tree and heads off to face him.
Be careful, Brother! They seem to be\ntargeting you alone!
Our enemies will never tire, and their\nspirit will never flag. The longer we fight,\nthe greater our disadvantage becomes.
Sounds like the only choice is to\njust plow straight through 'em.
Though true, I fear it will be a task\nof no mean difficulty.
Laxi! Where the hell have you been?!
Apologies. Preparations took longer\nthan initially anticipated.
Remote unit reporting in.\nReception quality satisfactory.\nBody control circuits all green.
Initiating shift to high-speed mode...\nShift complete. Commencing operation!
No abnormalities reported in limb or\nbody systems, so here I goooo!
By the Goddess, what speed...\nHe's twice as fast as the other androids!
Be quick, Mascula; the remote control\nsystem can only run for limited time.
I know! Preparing to initiate\ncommunication jamming now!
Time for you guys to take a nap!
That went WAY better than I thought!
The hell? Ya took down every damn\nandroid by yer lonesome!

Actually, I shocked their control circuits,
so they'll only be out of commission for a
little bit—but it should give us the time
we need to plan our next move.
But how the hell are you in that body?!
Ha ha! It's all thanks to Chelle.
Eee hee hee hee! I'm tickled to report that\nboth the start-up and combat experiments\nwere a smashing success!
It appears we have a powerful new\ncomrade on our side.
Finlorda, let me thank you once again\nfor your gracious cooperation.
I was glad to be of service.
How in the name'a ham did ya do this,\nChelle? I thought Mascula's old body\nwas in the crapper for good!

His body was damaged, yes, but not,
as you so delicately put it, ＂in the crapper.＂
So I collected the body and had my
research division in Chanzelia repair it.
However, we lacked the technology to\nreproduce the control circuit, which made\nit little more than an interesting toy.
Despite this, I had it loaded on the\nGran Fiore in the hopes I might discover\nsome way to make use of it.
At Princess Chelle's request, I applied\nfaerie magic to the control circuit,\nwhich amplified the signal.
And that gave Mascula the ability to\nmove about freely once more?
Is Mascula's heart still in Laxi's body?
But the faerie magic makes it possible\nfor me to control my old body remotely.
It sure is. Er, but it DOES demand\na lot more energy than normal.
As such, there is a limited amount of time\nin which he can operate the remote unit.
Still, this means I can help everyone\nout even more now, which is great!
Speaking of which, do you have a second\nto speak with Laxi and me, Maestro?
Of course. What do you need?
...We androids are artificial constructs,\nbuilt by humans.
But you treated us as more than just\nweapons, Maestro.
It was you who taught us that we could\nfight for a future WE wanted, even though\nwe were artificially created.
And you're still that same Maestro now.
So cheer up! We'll still be with you\njust like always.
We will create a world of peace,\nand we will do so at your side.
Well, since we're confessin' stuff now,\nI got something to say to ya, boss.
After we went back to the Halidom from\nthe border, I... Well, I doubted ya.\nNo nice way to say it.
But I ain't gonna make that mistake again.

Hell, if the worst comes to pass and ya
turn into the Other, we'll just kick yer butt
up and down the street until ya come back
to yer senses! Bwaaa ha ha ha!
If you stray from the right path, we will\nguide you back—just as you did for me.
I shall be ever at your side, Your Highness,\nand I implore you not to deviate from the\ngoal to which you have dedicated yourself.
(They're showing support in order to\nlift my spirit and keep me going...)
All right. I've come to a decision.
I want to go to the Sacred Tree and see\nwhat my father left for me there.
I need to know what he was thinking.
And I want you all to come with me.
Let us go discover Father's true thoughts!
Well, with that decided, let us finish\npreparations and set out.
It is my attendant—and he seems\nto be in something of a panic.
A force led by Jinlorda has appeared at\nthe Sacred Tree and launched an attack!

They are attempting to hold them off,
but I fear they cannot do so for long.
Also, Nedrick has been spotted amidst
the attacking force.
Why would Nedrick attack the Sacred Tree?
Additionally, there are reports that both\nthe Auspex and the fourth scion of the\nAlberian royal family are also present.
That cat's about as pliable as a stone slab.\nWhy's he playin' along with Nedrick?
I'm not sure—but it's Valyx we're talking\nabout, so he must have a plan.
Intending to ascend the Sacred Tree\nand make off with the Dawnshard?\nYes, that is my suspicion as well.
The Dawnshard of this world\nis in the Sacred Tree?!
But that makes no sense. Sacred shards\nare the shattered pieces of His Majesty\nAlberius's sword, are they not?
That is indeed what you in South Grastaea\nwere taught about the shards, but I fear it\nis a misconstruction of the actual history.
In truth, sacred shards are clumps of mana\nabsorbed by the Sacred Tree and given\ncrystalline form.
And every several hundred years, a shard\nknown as the Dawnshard is produced\nat the summit of the tree.
So why does Nedrick seek it now?
So he can forge a new pact with his wyrm.
Nedrick has a pactwyrm?! Er, but wait.\nIf that's the case, why does he need\nto swear a NEW pact?
Because the initial dragonpact\nNedrick swore was incomplete.
Nedrick's pactwyrm is Bahamut,\nthe Wyrm of Genesis.
Bahamut is an extremely dangerous\ndragon for a man to forge a pact with.
And I fear I've no idea what will happen\nif this new pact is undertaken.
I cannot even say whether or not\nNedrick will survive the process.
Regardless, we cannot stand idly by.\nWe must hurry to the Sacred Tree!
There's more, sire. We've also had\ndisquieting activities in the kingdom's\nvarious villages
A number of faeries are taking advantage\nof Jinlorda's absence to plot insurrection.
And without the king present, the only one\nwho can put a stop to the situation is you.
Man, this kingdom is a MESS.
Since my son became regent, he has been\nsteadfast in his pursuit of various reforms,\nand there are many who oppose him.
Still, the timing of a rebellion under these\ncircumstances is a little TOO convenient.\nThere must be more to it.
Finlorda, will you entrust the matter\nof the Dawnshard to us?
So long as he has Zethia,\nconflict with Nedrick is inevitable.
I'll stop both your son and Nedrick\nand protect the Dawnshard.
I concur. This is the most appropriate \ncourse of action given the situation.
I am sorry to place this burden upon you,\nbut I fear we have little choice.
I will send a messenger to the guardians\nin advance of your arrival. Please join up\nwith them when you arrive.
And while time is of the essence,\nthe day has slipped away from us.
Please feel free to make use of my manor.\nRest yourselves so you are ready for the\nevents that are to come on the morrow.
Thank you, Finlorda. In that case,\nwe set out at dawn.
